	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />If you want to hit something, make sure you are assisting on the main tank. Furthermore, wait until he's clearly established his target. Sometimes folks assist too soon. The main target may have mistargetted while rushing, or he's simply trying to get all mobs on him before he turns back to the primary target. Wait a bit and /assist several times to be sure of your target.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Just wanted to add a little something to this.<br />
<br />
Typing /assist off, will allow you to press your button without autoattack turning on.  This way you can spam the button untill your sure the MT has his target.</p>
	
	
	
